Input: employee_sales.csv with employee_id, Month, Revenue

Task:

Calculate total revenue per employee

result1=emp_df.groupby('employee_id')['Revenue'].sum()
result1

Find employee with highest revenue per month
result2=emp_df.loc[emp_df.groupby('Month')['Revenue'].idxmax()].reset_index()
result2

Optional: Plot bar chart of top 5 employees by total revenue

emp_df.groupby('employee_id')['Revenue'].sum().nlargest(5).plot(kind='bar')
